summary: This is an FBI Evidence of Custody form for electronic surveillance (ELSUR) materials, likely related to intercepts in the Epstein case. It indicates the transfer of magnetic tape evidence for permanent storage, with references to Title III intercepts and consensual monitoring.
keyFacts: The document is an FBI Evidence of Custody form for electronic surveillance (ELSUR) materials.
It references Title III court-authorized intercepts and consensual monitoring intercepts.
Magnetic tape evidence was transferred for permanent storage, indicating preservation of intercepted communications.
The form includes signatures and dates for chain of custody documentation.
The document is part of the Epstein case file, suggesting intercepted communications were collected as evidence.
